                                                        TCP/IP model

1.Application layer
•	Combines OSI’s Application, Presentation, and Session layers
Protocols :SFTP, NFS,HTTP, FTP, Telnet, NTP,DHCP, PING, HTTPS,SMTP, POP3, IMAP,ICMP, SSH, RDP,DNS, SSL, TLS


2.Transport layer
•	Handles TCP (reliable) & UDP (fast, unreliable).
                               TCP / UDP


3.Internet layer (Network layer)
•	 Routing, IP addressing (IP, ARP, ICMP)


4.Network access layer (Physical layer)
•	Combines OSI’s Data Link & Physical layers
•	 Ethernet, Fiber,Routers, Switches...
